Road Closed: **UPDATE - Tree Removal along Camino de la Tierra at Green Fields School - Pima County Ariz. (Sept. 15)  Pima County Department of Transportation discovered a large bee hive today in one of the trees designated for removal. The hive has been treated but will require 36 hours before they can be moved. The work schedule remains the same however the road closure has been pushed back slightly.As a reminder the trees identified by the Department are considered to be in a vulnerable condition and have become a public safety concern. Consequently several trees along Camino de la Tierra will be removed from the county right of way.Schedule: work will be performed between September 14 and September 18. Work hours are 7:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.**Road Closure: Camino de la Tierra between Mulberry Tree Lane and Las Palmas Drive will be closed on Thursday September 17 and Friday September 18 from 7 a.m. and 4 p.m. to allow heavy equipment and haul vehicles to safely move around the work zone.
